()“Clashes” ka matlab simple shabdon me takraav ya conflict hota hai.
Software/Technical context me clash ka matlab hai conflict ya takraav jo code, version, ya resources ke beech hota hai.
Thoda aur detail me samjhaun:-

()Code Merge Clash / Conflict:-
Jab do developers ek hi file me alag-alag changes karte hain aur unhe ek saath merge karna padta hai.
Agar Git ya kisi version control me system decide nahi kar paata ki kaunsa change rakha jaye, to merge conflict aata hai.

Example:-
Dev A ne line 10 me value = 5 kiya
Dev B ne line 10 me value = 10 kiya
→ Merge karte waqt clash hoga.

()Resource Clash:-
Jab do processes ya applications ek hi resource (jaise memory, file, network port) use karna chahte hain.
Example:-
Do programs ek hi file me write kar rahe hain → clash hoga,
Ek port pe do services bind karne ki koshish → clash hoga.

()Dependency Clash (Version Clash):-
Definition: Jab ek project me alag-alag libraries ya modules ki version requirements ek dusre se conflict kar rahi hoti hain.
Problem: Agar ye clash resolve nahi hota, to project build fail ho sakta hai ya runtime pe errors aayenge.

Example:-
Project me do libraries hain:-
Library A ko Library X v1.0 chahiye
Library B ko Library X v2.0 chahiye
Ab project me ek hi Library X ki version install hogi.
Isliye ya to build fail hoga ya run-time pe unexpected behavior aayega.
Real-life Example (Maven/Java):-

<dependency>
    <groupId>com.example</groupId>
    <artifactId>library-a</artifactId>
    <version>1.0</version>
</dependency>
<dependency>
    <groupId>com.example</groupId>
    <artifactId>library-b</artifactId>
    <version>2.0</version>
</dependency>
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
()name clashes kya hai?
Simple Explanation:-
Programming me har variable, function, ya class ka ek unique naam hona chahiye scope ke andar.
Agar same naam do jagah define ho jaye → name clash ho jata hai.
Ye compile-time error ya unexpected behavior cause kar sakta hai.

Example 1: Variables (Java):-
int x = 5;
int x = 10; // Name clash, compiler error
------------------------------------------------------------------
Example 2: Functions (Python):-
def greet():
    print("Hello")

def greet():
    print("Hi")  # Name clash, pehle wala overwrite ho jayega
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Example 3: Classes:-
package com.example.a;
class Person {}

package com.example.b;
class Person {} // Agar dono same package me ho to clash.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------